# Casey asset workflow

When editing or regenerating Casey assets:

- Do not hand-edit PNG pixels. Use:
  - `cases/scripts/fix-casey-transparency.py`
  - `cases/scripts/install-casey-pngs.sh`
- If you change `cases/scripts/fix-casey-transparency.py`, run `npm run test:static` after regeneration.
- Ensure floor/stage and checkerboard constraints remain enforced by static checks:
  - `tests/static/assert-casey-floor-matte*.mjs`
  - `tests/static/assert-casey-no-checker*.mjs`
- If a task claims the hub/coach visuals are fixed, also include evidence from the relevant static checks.

